1
00:00:06,020 --> 00:00:07,220
Say it again.

2
00:00:10,120 --> 00:00:11,120
Wataru.

3
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:14,300
Move in...

4
00:00:15,210 --> 00:00:16,210
with me.

5
00:00:18,180 --> 00:00:19,180
Yeah.

6
00:00:19,900 --> 00:00:20,900
I'd love to.

7
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:16,600
"Countdown To Yes"

8
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:21,800
(November 23, 2025)

9
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:36,700
(AFTER STORY: Countdown to Yes)

10
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:56,700
Morning.

11
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:21,800
Hey.

12
00:03:22,810 --> 00:03:23,810
What's up?

13
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:27,860
Just wanted to say hi.

14
00:03:29,090 --> 00:03:31,370
Right. Morning.

15
00:03:33,670 --> 00:03:34,790
I'm gonna go brush my teeth.

16
00:04:09,330 --> 00:04:10,330
Good morning.

17
00:04:12,850 --> 00:04:13,850
Morning.

18
00:04:16,620 --> 00:04:18,740
This is so embarrassing...
Hugging is so embarrassing.

19
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:24,960
What's gotten into you?

20
00:04:27,170 --> 00:04:29,170
I just realized all over again
how much I like you.

21
00:04:43,610 --> 00:04:45,510
Give it here! It's gonna drip!
It's dripping!

22
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:46,750
Give it to me.

23
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:47,920
I can't see.

24
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:50,060
I can't see anything.

25
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:51,790
Yes, you can.

26
00:04:58,330 --> 00:04:59,990
Okay.

27
00:05:01,190 --> 00:05:02,190
Ah...

28
00:05:04,850 --> 00:05:05,850
- There.
- Thanks.

29
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,320
Wait a sec.

30
00:05:12,321 --> 00:05:13,840
Ow.

31
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,600
Got it on.

32
00:05:16,510 --> 00:05:17,850
How are you so good at that?

33
00:05:17,940 --> 00:05:19,240
Comes with being a salaryman.

34
00:05:19,260 --> 00:05:20,260
Does that even matter?

35
00:05:21,990 --> 00:05:23,420
Oh, wait, Minato.

36
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:24,700
Hold on.

37
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:34,250
Should I wear something
a bit more formal?

38
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:36,310
Nah, you're fine.

39
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:37,400
Why?

40
00:05:37,401 --> 00:05:38,509
Usually you're there with me,

41
00:05:38,510 --> 00:05:40,370
but today it's just us solo.

42
00:05:40,670 --> 00:05:41,870
Hot, hot!

43
00:05:44,570 --> 00:05:45,570
It'll be fine.

44
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,000
Sorry I can't make it today.

45
00:05:47,130 --> 00:05:48,230
Work stuff, right?

46
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,800
Take some good photos for me.

47
00:05:50,010 --> 00:05:51,010
You got it.

48
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:57,830
I'll check out some furniture
on my way back.

49
00:05:58,140 --> 00:05:59,180
That would be a huge help.

50
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,339
We really need to decide soon.

51
00:06:00,340 --> 00:06:01,820
Or we won't be ready in time to move.

52
00:06:04,460 --> 00:06:05,990
About that camera shelf...

53
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:07,640
Should we get a bigger one?

54
00:06:08,290 --> 00:06:09,750
Let's just splurge on a nice one.

55
00:06:10,570 --> 00:06:13,500
Actually, I want a whole room
for my photography.

56
00:06:13,910 --> 00:06:16,260
To keep my gear and hang up prints.

57
00:06:16,970 --> 00:06:19,460
We could just turn the living room
into a permanent gallery.

58
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:20,800
The living room?

59
00:06:20,850 --> 00:06:22,420
- Is that okay?
- Why not?

60
00:06:22,790 --> 00:06:24,150
It's our home, after all.

61
00:06:24,770 --> 00:06:26,920
Now you've got me overthinking it.

62
00:06:27,610 --> 00:06:29,610
The list of things I want to do
just keeps growing.

63
00:06:30,950 --> 00:06:32,530
I found a pretty nice sofa.

64
00:06:41,110 --> 00:06:42,210
It's okay, I guess, but...

65
00:06:42,590 --> 00:06:43,840
I wish it were a bit softer.

66
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:45,730
A bit softer, huh?

67
00:06:46,850 --> 00:06:47,850
Got it.

68
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:49,209
I'll keep looking.

69
00:06:49,210 --> 00:06:50,520
Oh, wait, actually...

70
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,840
It's your favorite color,
and the vibe is perfect.

71
00:06:53,090 --> 00:06:54,090
It's great.

72
00:06:54,091 --> 00:06:55,500
Thanks for looking for me.

73
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:57,160
Are you sure?
Yeah.

74
00:06:58,490 --> 00:06:59,490
Let's eat.

75
00:07:04,420 --> 00:07:05,420
Let's eat.

76
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:07,840
Wallet, phone, keys...

77
00:07:08,290 --> 00:07:09,500
- Got 'em!
- Good.

78
00:07:11,010 --> 00:07:12,010
I forgot something.

79
00:07:13,130 --> 00:07:14,530
Ah, my phone! Thank god.

80
00:07:18,340 --> 00:07:20,960
How did we handle chores
back when we lived together?

81
00:07:21,510 --> 00:07:22,790
Whoever noticed it first did it.

82
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,200
Oh, right.

83
00:07:24,410 --> 00:07:26,640
But you ended up doing
almost everything.

84
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,550
I barely helped at all.

85
00:07:28,850 --> 00:07:29,850
Is that how it was?

86
00:07:30,830 --> 00:07:32,670
Let's set some real rules this time.

87
00:07:33,290 --> 00:07:34,500
Rules, huh?

88
00:07:35,730 --> 00:07:36,760
For cooking...

89
00:07:37,050 --> 00:07:39,120
Whoever gets home first makes dinner.

90
00:07:39,410 --> 00:07:41,000
Don't force yourself.

91
00:07:41,690 --> 00:07:43,180
We'll take turns with laundry.

92
00:07:43,650 --> 00:07:45,209
Or assign specific days.

93
00:07:45,210 --> 00:07:46,230
That's more fair.

94
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:48,699
Can't we just do it when we see it?

95
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:50,350
Then it'll just be like before.

96
00:07:50,670 --> 00:07:52,330
I want to pull my weight too.

97
00:07:57,850 --> 00:07:59,060
Even if we're fighting,

98
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,510
we always say good morning and goodnight.

99
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:03,310
I can do that.

100
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:05,390
But that's not what I meant.

101
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:08,250
A kiss before you leave.

102
00:08:08,490 --> 00:08:09,490
Ah...

103
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:11,290
No way! Absolutely not!

104
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:12,760
If we're doing that,

105
00:08:12,990 --> 00:08:16,399
then you're limited to one yogurt a day.

106
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:19,450
What? Come on, at least three...

107
00:08:19,570 --> 00:08:21,360
No. Definitely not.

108
00:08:21,570 --> 00:08:23,000
That's not healthy.

109
00:08:28,810 --> 00:08:29,810
Well...

110
00:08:30,310 --> 00:08:31,310
I'm heading out.

111
00:08:31,311 --> 00:08:33,280
Okay, have a good day.

112
00:08:39,870 --> 00:08:41,600
See, this is what I mean...

113
00:08:43,310 --> 00:08:44,510
That's so not fair.

114
00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:46,080
Totally unfair.

115
00:08:52,570 --> 00:08:53,570
Oh, man.

116
00:09:00,820 --> 00:09:02,870
It's your favorite color,
and the vibe is perfect.

117
00:09:03,220 --> 00:09:04,000
It's great.

118
00:09:04,001 --> 00:09:05,850
Thanks for looking for me.

119
00:09:30,110 --> 00:09:31,366
Sorry I'm the only one here today...

120
00:09:31,390 --> 00:09:32,680
What are you talking about?

121
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:34,650
I wanted to see you anyway.

122
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:35,920
Up we go.

123
00:09:35,990 --> 00:09:36,990
Here, these are for you.

124
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,310
This is so much... Are you sure?
Of course.

125
00:09:40,490 --> 00:09:42,540
We had a great harvest this year.

126
00:09:42,940 --> 00:09:45,130
Thank you. I'll take them, then.

127
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:51,590
So, how's it going?

128
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:53,140
Is the move coming along?

129
00:09:54,070 --> 00:09:56,420
We're still in the planning stages.

130
00:09:57,570 --> 00:09:59,199
Oh, for your housewarming gift,

131
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,009
I was thinking of an electric griddle.

132
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:02,110
What do you think?

133
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,600
Shio-kun and the others
said they're getting us one.

134
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:07,149
Good thing I asked first.

135
00:10:07,150 --> 00:10:08,479
I almost bought the same thing.

136
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,609
That was close.

137
00:10:09,610 --> 00:10:11,050
You don't have to go to any trouble.

138
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:12,449
You've already given us so much.

139
00:10:12,450 --> 00:10:13,679
It's fine.

140
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:14,800
Wataru is in your hands now.

141
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,190
That boy...

142
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,249
He wears his heart on his sleeve,

143
00:10:19,250 --> 00:10:21,256
but he never says what's actually
on his mind when it matters, right?

144
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:22,280
Are you doing okay?

145
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:24,050
He's not being a handful, is he?

146
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,440
Not at all.

147
00:10:26,260 --> 00:10:27,460
Oh, but...

148
00:10:28,140 --> 00:10:31,780
This morning, I showed him
a photo of a sofa I liked.

149
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,770
He said, "It's great,"

150
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,900
but his face said
something else entirely.

151
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:40,300
It was so obvious
that he wasn't into it.

152
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:41,399
Exactly.

153
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,010
He's always been like that.

154
00:10:45,850 --> 00:10:47,770
When he was just a little thing,

155
00:10:48,210 --> 00:10:49,320
he'd eat his carrots,

156
00:10:49,697 --> 00:10:51,697
and even though he looked
like he was about to gag,

157
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,879
I'd ask, "Oh, do you hate them?"

158
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:54,620
And then...

159
00:10:54,690 --> 00:10:56,090
He'd tell me they were delicious.

160
00:10:56,370 --> 00:10:58,570
With a face that said they were awful.

161
00:10:59,470 --> 00:11:00,470
Why would he do that?

162
00:11:00,670 --> 00:11:05,190
Well... probably because
he knew I liked carrots.

163
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:07,860
He's always been too considerate
for his own good.

164
00:11:09,470 --> 00:11:11,110
In times like that...

165
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:12,480
What did you do?

166
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:13,920
Hmm...

167
00:11:15,110 --> 00:11:16,110
Oh, I know!

168
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:17,250
We'd play "Telephone."

169
00:11:19,990 --> 00:11:22,280
Hello? Is this Wataru-kun?

170
00:11:23,190 --> 00:11:25,680
This is the Truth Recovery Center.

171
00:11:28,140 --> 00:11:30,330
We'll keep your secret from Mommy.

172
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:32,590
Please tell us how you really feel.

173
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:35,870
When I did that, he'd be honest.

174
00:11:37,012 --> 00:11:39,880
He'd say, "I don't actually
like carrots that much."

175
00:11:42,220 --> 00:11:43,220
That's so cute.

176
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:46,570
Yeah, but that sweetness of his...

177
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:49,880
I worry it might become
a burden for you.

178
00:11:51,930 --> 00:11:52,950
I'm happy.

179
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,260
Being with Wataru,

180
00:11:55,590 --> 00:11:57,870
even the smallest things are fun.

181
00:11:58,500 --> 00:11:59,500
It's easy.

182
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:03,560
So I want him to feel easy too.

183
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:07,581
With me... I want him to feel
like he can tell me anything.

184
00:12:14,790 --> 00:12:16,750
How wonderful.

185
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:18,820
Huh?

186
00:12:19,190 --> 00:12:20,190
Oh, right.

187
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,960
I have to give this to you too.

188
00:12:22,610 --> 00:12:23,610
Here.

189
00:12:25,270 --> 00:12:26,590
- Can I open it?
- Of course.

190
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:33,210
I saw it while on a walk.
Isn't it cute?

191
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,480
I thought it'd be perfect
for you and Wataru.

192
00:12:36,510 --> 00:12:37,510
Wow.

193
00:12:37,710 --> 00:12:39,500
There are so many.

194
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:42,049
Everyone wants us to have
matching stuff.

195
00:12:42,050 --> 00:12:43,810
These are all matching charms
people gave us.

196
00:12:45,790 --> 00:12:47,710
Oh, wow, that's impressive.

197
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:51,710
That one's from my grandparents'
vacation.

198
00:12:51,780 --> 00:12:53,780
I see. What about this one?

199
00:12:53,890 --> 00:12:55,540
The manager gave us that.

200
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:56,780
And this?

201
00:12:57,050 --> 00:12:58,280
My older brother gave me that.

202
00:12:58,310 --> 00:13:00,020
I see. It's cute.

203
00:13:00,340 --> 00:13:01,530
What about this one?

204
00:13:01,770 --> 00:13:05,280
We bought that together
at Nasu Nasu Shoppi.

205
00:13:05,340 --> 00:13:07,200
Ah, so you went together.

206
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:27,060
(Wataru: Got a ton of vegetables!)

207
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:44,000
(Minato: That's a lot!
(How should we cook them?)

208
00:13:56,050 --> 00:13:57,050
Hello?

209
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:58,240
What's up?

210
00:13:58,790 --> 00:13:59,790
Hello.

211
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:01,500
Is this Wataru-kun?

212
00:14:02,060 --> 00:14:03,060
Huh?

213
00:14:03,660 --> 00:14:04,660
This is...

214
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:06,520
The Truth Recovery Center.

215
00:14:09,820 --> 00:14:11,990
My mom told you something, didn't she?

216
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:15,520
We'll keep your secret from Minato.

217
00:14:19,730 --> 00:14:21,900
Please tell us how you really feel.

218
00:14:24,190 --> 00:14:26,310
You can't just put me on the spot...

219
00:14:27,220 --> 00:14:28,220
In your daily life,

220
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,850
is there anything you're worried
or unhappy about?

221
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,330
Well, if I had to say...

222
00:14:41,370 --> 00:14:42,370
Yes?

223
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,030
This morning...

224
00:14:44,740 --> 00:14:46,410
I wanted to wake up before Minato.

225
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:51,540
I love waking up

226
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:54,360
to the smell of coffee.

227
00:14:58,180 --> 00:14:59,630
That feeling of happiness...

228
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:02,060
I wanted Minato to feel it too.

229
00:15:04,620 --> 00:15:06,150
I was going to have the coffee ready

230
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:08,710
before he even got out of bed.

231
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:10,500
But I failed again.

232
00:15:13,090 --> 00:15:15,600
I'll let him know to sleep in tomorrow.

233
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:17,770
And when you hug me...

234
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:19,120
I'm happy.

235
00:15:19,490 --> 00:15:20,490
Really happy.

236
00:15:21,290 --> 00:15:22,910
So I want to do the same for you,

237
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,320
but I'm just not good at it.

238
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:29,520
Understood.

239
00:15:29,700 --> 00:15:30,700
I'll pass that along.

240
00:15:31,230 --> 00:15:33,330
Also, about the move...

241
00:15:33,820 --> 00:15:35,380
I keep talking about big ideas,

242
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:37,166
but when it comes to the actual work,

243
00:15:37,190 --> 00:15:39,160
I've left everything to Minato.

244
00:15:40,020 --> 00:15:41,470
I feel bad about it.

245
00:15:48,730 --> 00:15:49,730
Hello?

246
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:50,780
Are you listening?

247
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:53,660
About that sofa...

248
00:15:54,830 --> 00:15:55,830
Ah, yes.

249
00:15:57,000 --> 00:16:00,260
I'm sure we can find a better one.

250
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:02,260
So,

251
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:04,400
should we keep looking?

252
00:16:07,490 --> 00:16:08,490
Yeah.

253
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:12,180
Let's go to the furniture store together.

254
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:14,120
We'll find one that's actually comfortable.

255
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,130
If I can pick it out with you,

256
00:16:16,390 --> 00:16:17,490
I'd be really happy.

257
00:16:20,510 --> 00:16:21,730
Then let's go together.

258
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,760
Let's not settle.

259
00:16:26,790 --> 00:16:28,530
We'll find something we both love.

260
00:16:31,890 --> 00:16:32,890
Okay.

261
00:16:36,980 --> 00:16:38,180
In the future,

262
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,440
we're bound to fight,

263
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:43,180
or be afraid to say what we're thinking.

264
00:16:45,340 --> 00:16:47,380
When that happens, let's talk
like this again, okay?

265
00:16:48,860 --> 00:16:49,860
Yeah.

266
00:16:54,820 --> 00:16:55,820
You know...

267
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:57,890
I want to be with you forever.

268
00:16:59,980 --> 00:17:01,580
Where did that come from?

269
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:04,920
I just felt like telling you.

270
00:17:07,370 --> 00:17:10,000
Aren't you the Truth Recovery Center?

271
00:17:11,920 --> 00:17:12,920
Fair point.

272
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,000
Well then,

273
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:19,260
see you at home.

274
00:17:26,290 --> 00:17:27,290
Wataru?

275
00:17:41,630 --> 00:17:42,630
I'm home.

276
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:46,240
Welcome back.

277
00:17:50,230 --> 00:17:51,230
Let me take those.

278
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:53,680
Ah.

279
00:18:13,360 --> 00:18:14,560
What should we make?

280
00:18:15,520 --> 00:18:16,960
Maybe some grilled veggies in dashi.

281
00:18:17,670 --> 00:18:18,670
Mhm.

282
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:21,220
I want to try making rice bran pickles too.

283
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:23,130
Like with carrots?

284
00:18:24,190 --> 00:18:25,910
Oh, wait, you don't like those.

285
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:28,470
That was when I was a kid.

286
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,860
I'm totally fine with them now.

287
00:18:46,990 --> 00:18:48,520
It's morning.

288
00:18:51,090 --> 00:18:52,260
This is the limit.

289
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:53,520
I see.

290
00:18:55,110 --> 00:18:56,260
Got it. You get me.

291
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:59,150
This part is so nerve-wracking.

292
00:19:22,630 --> 00:19:23,630
Okay! Cut!

293
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:25,600
Perfect.

294
00:19:44,370 --> 00:19:46,119
No, we won't make it.

295
00:19:46,120 --> 00:19:47,120
Cut.

296
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:48,300
Okay.

297
00:19:48,530 --> 00:19:49,530
That's a wrap.

298
00:20:08,860 --> 00:20:10,450
Being my personal photographer...

299
00:20:15,870 --> 00:20:17,600
These shots are amazing... so good...

300
00:20:25,330 --> 00:20:26,520
It's hard to see.

301
00:20:26,650 --> 00:20:27,650
Which one?

302
00:21:53,290 --> 00:21:55,360
And with that,

303
00:21:55,560 --> 00:21:58,800
"Countdown To Yes"

304
00:21:59,460 --> 00:22:00,829
is officially wrapped!

305
00:22:00,830 --> 00:22:01,880
Great job, everyone!

306
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:11,940
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat.

307
00:22:13,380 --> 00:22:14,590
Oh, it's leaking.

308
00:22:16,020 --> 00:22:17,040
What?

309
00:22:18,610 --> 00:22:19,610
Tissue.

310
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Thanks.

311
00:22:23,170 --> 00:22:24,270
You got some on you too.

312
00:22:24,770 --> 00:22:26,440
- No, I didn't.
- Yes, you did.

313
00:22:27,370 --> 00:22:28,689
Mhm, thanks.

314
00:22:28,690 --> 00:22:29,740
Over here too.

315
00:22:30,010 --> 00:22:31,010
Mhm.

316
00:22:33,660 --> 00:22:35,710
Crap! It fell out!

317
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:42,599
(Thank you all so much for your support.
Until we meet again... - Yokoi Minato)

318
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:45,000
(Thanks for everything! See you next time!!
- Nakano Wataru)
